{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chart-page-js","path":"/stacked-area-chart","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Stacked area chart shows multiple data curves and fills the area between them. The curve with less variation is typically drawn at the bottom, closer to the X-axis. Stacked area charts are known to be difficult to perceive because the human eye does not judge area shown relative to a curved line as well as relative to a straight line.<sup id=\"fnref-1\"><a href=\"#fn-1\" class=\"footnote-ref\">1</a></sup> The fill in a stacked area chart is necessary for readability. <sup id=\"fnref-2\"><a href=\"#fn-2\" class=\"footnote-ref\">2</a></sup></p>\n<!--more-->\n<h2 id=\"references\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#references\" aria-label=\"references permalink\" class=\"anchorLink before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>References</h2>\n<div class=\"footnotes\">\n<hr>\n<ol>\n<li id=\"fn-1\">\n<p>Thudt, Alice, et al. <a href=\"https://dx.doi.org/10.20380/GI2016.21\">\"Assessing the Readability of Stacked Graphs.\"</a> 2016. <a href=\"https://hal.inria.fr/hal-01587962/document\">PDF</a></p>\n<a href=\"#fnref-1\" class=\"footnote-backref\">↩</a>\n</li>\n<li id=\"fn-2\">\n<p>Koponen, Juuso, and Jonatan Hildén. <a href=\"https://shop.aalto.fi/p/971-data-visualization-handbook/\"><em>Data visualization handbook.</em></a> Aalto korkeakoulusäätiö, 2019 p. 210 </p>\n<a href=\"#fnref-2\" class=\"footnote-backref\">↩</a>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</div>","excerpt":"Stacked area chart shows m